                            <comment id="14145156" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2014 18:11:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1627108 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1627108&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1627108&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2379&quot; title=&quot;glyphlist_ext is not OSGI compatible&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2379&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2379&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Removed support for glyphlist_ext property&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14145160" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2014 18:13:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve chosen to throw an UnsupportedOperationException if &quot;glyphlist_ext&quot; is set, so that users upgrading to 2.0 don&apos;t get silent errors. We also print a message explaining that GlyphList.DEFAULT.addGlyphs(Properties) has to be called instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283752" author="mato" created="Tue, 20 Jan 2015 12:02:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree that glyphlist_ext property is not the best suited for OSGi, however it was working very well with command-line tools like ExtractText. Please could you consider adding it back, or introduce some mechanism how user can specify its own glyphlist from command-line tools without a need to dig into Java source code?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14284089" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 20 Jan 2015 17:40:59 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;introduce some mechanism how user can specify its own glyphlist from command-line tools without a need to dig into Java source code&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a nice idea, feel free to open a new JIRA issue proposing that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14285414" author="mato" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2015 09:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Before posting a new request, I would like to think a bit about the possible design. I have some OSGi background and I&apos;m aware of the cost of properly using classloaders, explicitly exporting classes, declaring dependencies... &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do we know why this OSGi-related problem was resolved by throwing an exception instead of keeping the glyphlist_ext property intact and simply documenting - use GlyphList.DEFAULT.addGlyphs(Properties) when working in OSGi or other complex application server environment where you load PDFBOX classes (not just instantiate objects) possibly multiple times with different configurations? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14286138" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2015 19:37:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We never should have used a system property here in the first place, as there was no need for it. We&apos;re cleaning up the API in 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14287182" author="mato" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2015 09:53:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Understood. I think adding -glyphlist &amp;lt;glyhplist file&amp;gt; to the PDFBox executables should do the trick. I would recommend to follow the Adobe&apos;s format of the glyphlist file using semicolon as a separator as was used by glyphlist_ext property. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
